838
01:53:34,347 --> 01:53:36,672
Do you copy? Damn it!

839
01:53:36,849 --> 01:53:40,467
Metropolis Tower, this is seaplane
November-Seven-Two-Four-One-Hotel.

840
01:53:40,645 --> 01:53:42,471
Do you copy?

841
01:53:44,357 --> 01:53:47,026
Lois! Are you all right?

842
01:53:47,443 --> 01:53:50,812
Yeah. What happened?

843
01:53:51,947 --> 01:53:54,569
- Superman.
- Where is he?

844
01:53:56,076 --> 01:53:57,321
He went back.

845
01:53:59,955 --> 01:54:02,162
- Richard, we have to turn around.
- What? No.

846
01:54:02,333 --> 01:54:04,954
- We have to turn around!
- We barely made it out of there.

847
01:54:05,127 --> 01:54:07,700
- Now you want me to go back?
- Yes, please!

848
01:54:08,464 --> 01:54:10,291
He'll die.

849
01:54:13,302 --> 01:54:15,176
All right, hold on.

850
01:54:32,696 --> 01:54:34,523
Kryptonite.

851
01:54:39,661 --> 01:54:41,618
You're asking yourself, "How?"

852
01:54:43,415 --> 01:54:48,373
Didrt your dad ever teach you
to look before you leap?

853
01:54:52,424 --> 01:54:55,378
Crystals. They're amazing, aren't they?

854
01:54:55,552 --> 01:54:58,802
They inerit the traits
of the minerals around them...

855
01:54:58,972 --> 01:55:03,764
...kind of like a son
ineriting the traits of his father!

856
01:55:06,563 --> 01:55:11,557
You took away five years of my life,
I'm just returning the favor!

857
01:55:15,071 --> 01:55:18,108
I'm still Superman!

858
01:55:26,749 --> 01:55:30,165
Get up! Come on!

859
01:57:02,219 --> 01:57:04,212
Now, fly.

860
01:58:05,323 --> 01:58:08,277
So long, Superman.

861
01:58:10,745 --> 01:58:13,829
Your leadership can stir others...

862
01:58:13,998 --> 01:58:16,157
...to their own capacities
for moral betterment.

863
01:58:16,334 --> 01:58:19,288
The human heart is still subject
to monstrous deceits.

864
01:58:22,924 --> 01:58:25,794
Our destruction could have been avoided.
At this very moment...

865
01:58:25,968 --> 01:58:27,593
...I could embrace you in my arms.

866
01:58:27,762 --> 01:58:30,169
Your help would be called for endlessly.
Remember me.

867
01:58:30,348 --> 01:58:33,681
Even for those tasks which human beings
could solve themselves.

868
01:58:44,111 --> 01:58:46,946
Remember me, Kal-EI.

869
01:58:47,114 --> 01:58:49,023
Remember me.

870
01:58:57,917 --> 01:58:59,660
Supermars down there.

871
01:59:00,669 --> 01:59:03,042
- You sure?
- Yeah.

872
01:59:13,515 --> 01:59:16,137
- Richard!
- Yeah, I saw him. Strap in.

873
01:59:44,880 --> 01:59:46,671
Lois!

874
01:59:48,008 --> 01:59:49,799
Don't move.

875
02:00:35,889 --> 02:00:37,928
Come on, come on, come on.

876
02:00:41,686 --> 02:00:43,394
Richard!

877
02:00:43,563 --> 02:00:44,938
I'm trying! It's too choppy!

878
02:00:54,073 --> 02:00:55,651
Oh, my God.

879
02:02:43,348 --> 02:02:45,341
How did you find me?

880
02:02:50,855 --> 02:02:52,480
Thank you.

881
02:03:07,455 --> 02:03:09,364
What are you doing?

882
02:03:12,543 --> 02:03:13,788
I have to go back.

883
02:03:16,506 --> 02:03:18,249
You're hurt!

884
02:03:28,726 --> 02:03:30,386
Goodbye, Lois.

885
02:04:40,797 --> 02:04:43,123
The technology on Krypton,
Superman 's home world...

886
02:04:43,300 --> 02:04:45,625
...was based on manipulating
the growth of crystals.

887
02:04:45,802 --> 02:04:47,178
Sounds like hocus-pocus to me.

888
02:04:47,346 --> 02:04:51,177
Well, naturally, to the primitive mind,
any sufficiently advanced technology...

889
02:04:51,349 --> 02:04:53,307
...would be indistinguishable from magic.

890
02:04:53,477 --> 02:04:56,892
But imagine: Cities, vehicles, weapons...

891
02:04:57,063 --> 02:04:59,554
...entire continents, all grown.

892
02:04:59,733 --> 02:05:01,476
Lex?

893
02:05:03,320 --> 02:05:06,439
Are billions of people really going to die?

894
02:05:12,954 --> 02:05:14,662
Yes.

895
02:05:42,025 --> 02:05:43,353
Lex, what's happening?

896
02:05:49,323 --> 02:05:50,948
Go, go, go. Get to the helicopter.

897
02:05:53,828 --> 02:05:56,200
Go! Out, out! Now!

898
02:05:59,375 --> 02:06:02,542
No, no, no, take nothing!
Take nothing! Go, go!

899
02:06:04,463 --> 02:06:06,041
Got it.

900
02:06:50,175 --> 02:06:51,753
Here.

901
02:07:15,659 --> 02:07:17,616
- What did you do?
- I'm sorry!

902
02:07:17,786 --> 02:07:19,364
No!

903
02:07:38,932 --> 02:07:42,515
- What did you do?
- I'm sorry!

904
02:11:42,089 --> 02:11:43,583
Watch it.

905
02:11:44,967 --> 02:11:47,173
- Clear a path.
- Clear the way.

906
02:11:47,720 --> 02:11:49,344
- Move!
- Trauma One.

907
02:11:50,723 --> 02:11:53,048
- Where we going?
- Trauma One. Here it is.

908
02:11:58,897 --> 02:12:00,605
Watch it!

909
02:12:08,448 --> 02:12:09,824
Got him!

910
02:12:13,495 --> 02:12:14,870
Okay, I think I got it.

911
02:12:19,459 --> 02:12:22,294
Penetrating side wound
to right part of lower back.

912
02:12:23,630 --> 02:12:24,793
No hemorrhage.

913
02:12:29,469 --> 02:12:30,798
Shock at 200.

914
02:12:30,971 --> 02:12:32,797
Is that enough? He's not human.

915
02:12:32,973 --> 02:12:34,633
All right, charge to three, 360.

916
02:12:34,808 --> 02:12:36,385
Clear!

917
02:13:07,048 --> 02:13:08,328
It's kind of morbid, Perry.

918
02:13:09,175 --> 02:13:11,631
Always be prepared.

919
02:13:14,013 --> 02:13:15,721
How is she?

920
02:13:35,243 --> 02:13:38,243
Thank you. Thanks, baby.

921
02:13:41,040 --> 02:13:42,285
- Lois?
- Yeah.

922
02:13:44,460 --> 02:13:46,369
We can leave whenever you're ready.

923
02:13:46,545 --> 02:13:48,123
I mean...

924
02:13:49,715 --> 02:13:51,708
